# WC2026 Qualification Prediction Engine — Cursor Rules

TypeScript monorepo for a cloud-native, event-sourced FIFA World Cup 2026 qualification and prediction platform.

## Architecture

- **Three bounded contexts (hard boundaries):**
  - BC1: Data Intake & Reconciliation (`workers/intake`, `workers/reconciliation`, `packages/identity`)
  - BC2: Official Qualification Engine (`packages/qualification`, `workers/qualification`) — deterministic only
  - BC3: Prediction & Scenario Engine (`packages/prediction`, `workers/prediction`) — probabilistic only
- BC2 and BC3 never share mutable state. Prediction reads qualification snapshots; it never writes them.
- All canonical types live in `packages/canonical`. Never redefine entity shapes locally.
- All domain events live in `packages/events` with Zod schemas. Validate at every boundary.
- Architectural changes require an ADR in `docs/adr/`.

## Package & Import Rules

- Import canonical types from `@wc2026/canonical`, events from `@wc2026/events`.
- Qualification math: `@wc2026/qualification` only (pure functions, zero I/O).
- Prediction math: `@wc2026/prediction` only.
- Provider payloads: validate with `@wc2026/zod-schemas` before any business logic.
- No provider-native IDs outside adapter/reconciliation layers — resolve via IdentityService first.
- No inline imports. All imports at top of file.

## Event Sourcing

- Raw provider payloads: append-only `raw_event_log`. Never update or delete.
- Corrections: append-only `CorrectionEvent`. Replay on top of provider state.
- Qualification/prediction snapshots: immutable insert-only rows.
- Fuzzy identity matches below threshold → quarantine queue. Never auto-write to canonical graph.

## Testing

- Add regression tests for every identity, qualification, or reconciliation bug fix.
- Qualification and prediction packages: pure function tests, CI-blocking.
- Property-based or snapshot tests for tie-breaking and calibration edge cases.
- MSW fixtures for provider HTTP in CI — no live API calls.

## Prohibited Patterns

```typescript
// BAD: prediction logic in qualification package
import { buildMatchPrediction } from "@wc2026/prediction"; // in packages/qualification

// BAD: provider ID in UI without resolution
const teamId = espnResponse.team.id; // use IdentityService.resolveToCanonical()

// BAD: destructive overwrite of raw provider data
await db.rawEvent.update({ where: { id }, data: payload });

// BAD: fuzzy auto-resolve
if (fuzzyScore > 0.5) await writeCanonical(id); // must quarantine below threshold
```

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] Official vs prediction logic in correct bounded context?
- [ ] Canonical types imported from `@wc2026/canonical`?
- [ ] Events validated with Zod at wire boundary?
- [ ] Identity resolved before canonical write?
- [ ] CorrectionEvents append-only with audit trail?
- [ ] Tests added for changed domain logic?
- [ ] ADR if architecture changed?
- [ ] Version bump (`npm run version:build`) if source changed?

See also: `.cursor/rules/architecture.mdc`, `bounded-contexts.mdc`, `testing.mdc`.
